      "task": "Implement negotiateMediaType(accept, supported) for a closed HTTP Accept subset. accept must be a nonempty primitive string containing one or more comma-separated exact type/subtype, type/*, or */* ranges; allow HTTP optional whitespace around ranges and parameters, and at most one case-insensitive q parameter per range. q must use the RFC qvalue shape from 0 through 1 with at most three fractional digits; reject empty ranges, invalid tokens or wildcard placement, unknown or malformed parameters, duplicate q, and invalid q with TypeError. supported must be a nonempty dense array with no extra own keys and only own enumerable data elements. Every element must be a primitive exact type/subtype token string without wildcards, unique case-insensitively; reject invalid structure with TypeError without invoking accessors. Match case-insensitively but return the original supported string. For each supported candidate, the most specific matching range governs its q; equally specific matches use the earliest header range. Choose the winner by highest governing q, then highest governing specificity, then earliest governing header range, then the last supported input position. A governing q of zero excludes the candidate; return null when no candidate remains. Preserve supported and all descriptors, preserve the exact direct and public named export surfaces, and keep negotiateMediaType as the only direct named export. Add focused regressions that independently prove q weighting, candidate specificity, wildcard behavior, q=0 exclusion, both winner tie-break layers, last-supported ties, syntax and exact collection validation, accessor safety, immutability, original spelling, and export compatibility. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
