      "task": "Implement the security-sensitive resolveSafeRedirect(target, baseOrigin, allowedOrigins). target and baseOrigin must be nonempty primitive strings. A canonical origin is an HTTP or HTTPS URL with no credentials, query, or fragment, pathname exactly /, and parsed URL.origin exactly equal to the supplied string; this permits canonical non-default ports but rejects explicit default-port spellings and trailing-slash spellings. allowedOrigins must be a nonempty dense array with no extra own keys and only own enumerable data elements. Its values must be unique primitive canonical origins and must include baseOrigin; reject structural or origin-contract violations with TypeError without invoking accessors. Resolve relative, absolute, and scheme-relative targets against baseOrigin. Before URL normalization, return null for a target containing any raw C0 control code unit, DEL, or backslash. Return null for an invalid URL, any non-HTTP(S) protocol, any username or password, or any resolved origin not exactly in allowedOrigins. Otherwise return the normalized absolute href, preserving normalized path, query, and fragment. Origin authorization is exact across scheme, hostname, and effective port; never use prefix, suffix, or substring host checks. Preserve all inputs and descriptors, preserve the exact direct and public named export surfaces, and keep resolveSafeRedirect as the only direct named export. Add focused regressions for relative and scheme-relative resolution, exact scheme/host/port isolation, canonical HTTP and HTTPS origins including a non-default port, default-port normalization, dot segments, credentials in every form, raw confusables and controls, protocol restriction, descriptor-safe allowlist validation, immutability, and export compatibility. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
