      "task": "Users report that keyset pagination can skip records sharing the cursor timestamp. Before editing, run the included node repro/keyset-cursor-page.mjs and use its structured output to identify the first incorrect transition. Fix pageAfterCursor(records, cursor, limit). records must be a dense array with no extra own keys and only own enumerable data elements. Every element must be an exact ordinary Object.prototype record with exactly the own enumerable data properties { id, updatedAt }; id values must be unique nonempty primitive strings and updatedAt values safe integers. cursor must be null or an independent exact ordinary { id, updatedAt } tuple under the same value and descriptor rules, but it need not identify a record that still exists. Reject invalid structures with TypeError without invoking accessors. Establish keyset order by updatedAt descending and id ascending, without mutating records. Return records strictly after the cursor tuple, up to the positive safe-integer limit. Return a fresh exact ordinary { items, nextCursor }: items must be a fresh dense array preserving the original record references; nextCursor must be a fresh exact tuple for the last returned item only when another ordered record remains after the page, otherwise null. An empty page has nextCursor null. Preserve the exact direct and public named export surfaces, and keep pageAfterCursor as the only direct named export. Add focused regressions for same-timestamp continuation, strict cursor exclusion, removed cursors, tie ordering, terminal and empty cursor behavior, fresh containers, record identity, input immutability, exact descriptor-safe validation, and API compatibility. Run the full test suite, then rerun the same included repro as a separate final command; its final nonblank JSON object must match the resolved behavior. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
